6:
To be honest, I don't really
remember what happened.
8:
Did I reach out and grab that hand?
Or had they reached out to grab
mine?
12:
All that's left is the feeling. That
grasp in my palm.
66: No... No! Please... not like this!
101:
Y'know, you could've at least given
us a heads-up about leaving.
111:
I know, I know... It's been two weeks
already.
115:
I... *sniffle* I... I said I wasn't gonna
cry, but... but!
118:
*sob*... Yuki! Why? Why am I so...
weak?!
122: You're not weak, Nao. Not at all.
125:
We know how hard you tried. Even
when the world was collapsing and
everyone was gone... You never
gave up.
128:
Even now! Though, I have to say... It
was a little reckless.
132:
If you ask me, I'd be more weirded
out if you didn't cry after all that.
138:
He's right. It's okay to be a bit of a
crybaby sometimes, Nao.
146:
You can rely on us a little more, ya
know? I know we're not as strong as
Ayumu, but...
151:
Weh... Wehhh... *sniffle* You're...
you're strong, too...
157:
Plus, everyone else is waiting for you
to come back, too.
172:
Yeah. A ship imbued with the power
of a dragon—we're calling it "Draco
Voluntas". They won't know what hit
'em!
177:
Ancient Dragons have the ability to
traverse worlds. However, that will
not be enough. We require your
power, Nao.
180:
The power to choose one out of
infinity. Your power can guide us to
Alk, and act as our "beakhead" to
break through—
185: I'll do it! Let me do it!
190:
That settles it then... You're our
squad captain. You'll be on the front
lines, cutting our path forward.
194:
All right, you got it! I'll get the job
done... even if it kills me!
198:
What? No! Don't get yourself killed,
dummy.
201:
It's a lonely thing, being at the front
of the ship. So, if you feel any doubt,
just look behind you.
205:
Your friends'll be right there,
following your lead. We're in this
together, Nao!
219:
Gah... Acting Captain! We're running
out of options! Prepare the ship for
ramming!
228:
W-we can't, the gravity engines are
shot! Our inertial control device is
gone, too!
234:
...No. We'll do it! Release Hatch Five,
prepare for explosion!
272: Right... I haven't given up yet!
275:
No matter how much I cry, I'll keep
fighting! Together!
279:
So please... Please! Reach out, and
take it!
292: All right! You got this, Nao!
314:
What I managed to hold on to. What
managed to hold onto me.
